
[1]brome

   BROME, n. [Gr. foetor.] A liquid of a deep red-brown color, very
   volatile,and having an ill smell, obtained from the mother-water of
   salt-works,and from the lixivia of the ashes of sea plants, by treating
   these solutions with chlorine. It has three times the density of water.
